  {
    "text": "Hexaploid amphiploids have the AACCDD genome composition, while octoploid amphiploids have AACCCCDD, AAAACCDD, or AABBCCDD compositions. The A, B, C, and D oat genomes differ in involvement in non-centromeric, intercalary translocations.",
    "entities": [],
    "relations": []
  },
