    "text": "Drought stress increased malondialdehyde (MDA) and hydrogen peroxide (H2O2) levels, with the highest accumulation in L3. Cultivar D maintained higher antioxidant enzyme activities (CAT, POD, SOD, APX), better photosynthetic performance, and greater chlorophyll retention than L3.",
